definition.value: A quinolinemonocarboxylic acid with broad-spectrum antibacterial activity against most gram-negative and gram-positive bacteria. Norfloxacin is bactericidal and its mode of action depends on blocking of bacterial DNA replication by binding itself to an enzyme called DNA gyrase.
An oxo monocarboxylic acid in which pentanoic acid is substituted at C-5 with an oxo group and a 3-azidopropylamino group.
